name: N-(9-fluorenylmethoxycarbonyloxy)succinimide
Reason: 9-Fluorenylmethoxycarbonyloxy group introduces a rigid structure with increased molecular weight and van der Waals forces, estimated at around +20 °C. The methoxy group introduces additional hydrogen bonding potential, estimated at around +5 °C. The carbonyl group introduces polar carbonyl interactions, estimated at around +40 °C. The fluorenyl group introduces additional pi-pi interactions and rigidity, estimated at around +30 °C. The succinimide group introduces additional hydrogen bonding potential, estimated at around +10 °C. The presence of these functional groups raises the melting point due to increased molecular weight, van der Waals forces, and hydrogen bonding.
